const sopSections=[
{id:'overview',num:'§1',name:'Overview',render:()=>`
<div class="sop-doc">
  <div class="sop-section-header">
    <div class="sop-section-num">Section 1</div>
    <div class="sop-section-name">Overview & How It Works</div>
    <div class="sop-section-desc">This SOP defines how the engineering team works with AI agents across the full development lifecycle. It is a living document — agents keep parts of it updated automatically.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="sop-callout info"><div class="sop-callout-icon">💡</div><div><strong>The core idea:</strong> Routine tasks (code review, ticket implementation, nightly QA, changelogs) are handled by named cloud agents running headlessly on Devin. Engineers focus on judgment: writing clear requirements, reviewing agent output, and making architectural decisions. Agents don't replace engineers — they eliminate the work engineers shouldn't be doing in the first place.</div></div>
  <div class="sop-h3">What a session actually is</div>
  <div class="sop-callout tip"><div class="sop-callout-icon">💡</div><div>Each agent run is a <strong>Devin session</strong> on its own cloud VM with a Shell, an embedded IDE, and a Browser (computer use). It keeps working after you close your laptop, runs your tests, and can attach a video recording of what it verified. <strong>Rule of thumb:</strong> if a task would take a competent engineer about three hours, Devin can usually do it — scope tickets accordingly.</div></div>
  <div class="sop-h3">The System at a Glance</div>
  <table class="sop-table">
    <tr><th>Layer</th><th>Tool</th><th>Role in this system</th></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Work intake</strong></td><td>Jira</td><td>Source of truth for all work. Acceptance criteria here is the agent's specification. Labels like <code>devin</code> trigger agents automatically.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Code &amp; review</strong></td><td>GitHub</td><td>All code lives here. Agents open PRs, respond to CI, and review changes. Branch protections apply to agents just like humans.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Agent runtime</strong></td><td>Devin Desktop</td><td>Agents run headlessly on cloud VMs. Each agent is a Scheduled Session + a Playbook. Triggered by cron, Jira labels, GitHub events, or Teams.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Control plane</strong></td><td>Microsoft Teams</td><td>All agents report here. Trigger any agent manually: <code>@Devin !review</code>. Receive nightly summaries, PR digests, QA reports.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Documentation</strong></td><td>Confluence</td><td>Agents keep it updated. Architecture Decision Records, runbooks, and release pages are written and maintained by agents after human approval.</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="sop-h3">The Flow</div>
  <table class="sop-table">
    <tr><th>Step</th><th>Who</th><th>What happens</th></tr>
    <tr><td>1. Write ticket</td><td>Engineer / PM</td><td>Clear acceptance criteria, Definition of Done, links to design docs. This is the agent's only specification.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>2. Label <code>devin</code></td><td>Engineer</td><td>Hermes picks up the ticket, implements it, opens a PR. Jira ticket moves to "In Review".</td></tr>
    <tr><td>3. Zeus reviews PR</td><td>Zeus (agent)</td><td>Automated first-pass review within minutes. Bug detection, CI triage, ticket context surfaced inline.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>4. Human review</td><td>Engineer</td><td>Reviews for business logic only. Zeus has already filtered out the boilerplate issues.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>5. Argus validates</td><td>Argus (agent)</td><td>Nightly regression + coverage enforcement. Any regressions filed as Jira tickets automatically.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>6. Atlas releases</td><td>Atlas (agent)</td><td>Friday: changelog compiled, release tagged, Confluence updated, Jira version closed, stakeholders notified.</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="sop-callout warning"><div class="sop-callout-icon">⚠️</div><div><strong>Important:</strong> Agents make mistakes. Always read PRs and review agent findings before merging. You remain accountable for everything that ships. Agents are a multiplier on your output, not a replacement for your judgment.</div></div>
</div>`},
{id:'workflow',num:'§2',name:'SDLC Workflow',render:()=>`
<div class="sop-doc">
  <div class="sop-section-header">
    <div class="sop-section-num">Section 2</div>
    <div class="sop-section-name">SDLC Workflow — Phase by Phase</div>
    <div class="sop-section-desc">What changed in each phase, and what your job now is.</div>
  </div>
  ${[
    {num:'01',name:'Architecture & Design',before:'Engineers write design docs manually in Confluence. Docs are rarely linked to Jira. Architecture knowledge is siloed.',now:'Devin generates Architecture Decision Records from Jira epics. Design docs are auto-published to Confluence, linked to the ticket. Ask Devin and DeepWiki replace manual codebase archaeology.',yourJob:['Write detailed Jira epics with clear requirements before design starts','Review and approve AI-generated Architecture Decision Records before they publish','Maintain <code>AGENTS.md</code> in each repo with architecture conventions and forbidden patterns','Use <code>@Devin !design-review</code> in Teams to review any proposed design against the codebase']},
    {num:'02',name:'Development',before:'Engineers use Devin Desktop as autocomplete only. Jira ↔ GitHub link is manual. Dev context lives in the engineer\'s head.',now:'Hermes picks up Jira tickets daily and implements them autonomously. Cascade is used for planning, then handed off to Devin cloud. Jira ↔ GitHub is synced automatically.',yourJob:['Write acceptance criteria with explicit Definition of Done — this is Hermes\'s only spec','Add the <code>devin</code> label to tickets that are ready — no open questions, no blockers','Review completed PRs for business logic (not style — Zeus handles that)','Unblock Hermes via Teams if it asks clarifying questions mid-task']},
    {num:'03',name:'Code Review',before:'PRs wait 24–48 hours for human review. Reviewers lack context from the original Jira ticket. CI failures block merge with no triage.',now:'Zeus reviews every PR within minutes of opening. CI failures are auto-triaged and fixed. Jira ticket and acceptance criteria appear inline on every PR.',yourJob:['Do not merge until Zeus has posted its review comment','Humans review for business logic only — Zeus filters out boilerplate issues first','Maintain <code>REVIEW.md</code> in your repo with team-specific review rules and patterns to flag','If Zeus misses something important, add it to <code>REVIEW.md</code> — not just a comment']},
    {num:'04',name:'Test & QA',before:'Manual QA regression. Test coverage is inconsistent. Bugs found late are expensive.',now:'Argus runs nightly regression across all repos. Tests are generated from acceptance criteria. Coverage is enforced automatically — merge is blocked if it drops.',yourJob:['Write acceptance criteria in testable form (Given/When/Then helps Argus generate better tests)','Add <code>!write-tests</code> label to tickets where coverage needs to increase','Check <code>#qa-alerts</code> every morning — triage any new Jira tickets Argus has filed','Do not delete tests to make coverage numbers look good — fix the underlying issue']},
    {num:'05',name:'Release & Deploy',before:'Release notes written manually. Runbooks in Confluence are outdated. Rollback decisions are tribal knowledge.',now:'Atlas compiles a categorized changelog every Friday, tags the release in GitHub, updates Confluence, and closes the Jira release version. Post-deploy monitoring is automated.',yourJob:['Close or defer all P1/P2 blockers before Friday — Atlas will halt if any exist','Review and approve Atlas\'s release notes before they publish externally','Do not manually tag releases in GitHub — Atlas owns this','Monitor <code>#incidents</code> after deploys — Themis and Atlas are watching 24/7']}
  ].map(p=>`
    <div class="sop-h3">${p.num}. ${p.name}</div>
    <table class="sop-table" style="margin-bottom:8px">
      <tr><th style="width:50%">Before</th><th style="width:50%">Now</th></tr>
      <tr><td>${p.before}</td><td>${p.now}</td></tr>
    </table>
    <div class="sop-h4">Your job</div>
    <div class="ruled-list" style="margin-bottom:20px">${p.yourJob.map(j=>`<div class="ruled-item"><div class="item-pip pip-neutral"></div><span>${j}</span></div>`).join('')}</div>
  `).join('')}
</div>`},
{id:'agents',num:'§3',name:'Agent Reference',render:()=>`
<div class="sop-doc">
  <div class="sop-section-header">
    <div class="sop-section-num">Section 3</div>
    <div class="sop-section-name">Agent Quick Reference</div>
    <div class="sop-section-desc">The six named agents, their schedules, and how to trigger them manually.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="sop-callout info"><div class="sop-callout-icon">💡</div><div><strong>How named agents work:</strong> Each agent is a Devin <strong>Scheduled Session</strong> + a <strong>Playbook</strong>. They run headlessly on cloud VMs. Trigger any agent manually from Teams: <code>@Devin !review</code>, <code>@Devin !implement PROJ-123</code>, <code>@Devin !release</code>. All agents report back to their designated Teams channel.</div></div>
  <table class="sop-table">
    <tr><th>Agent</th><th>Role</th><th>Auto-runs</th><th>Teams trigger</th><th>Reports to</th></tr>
    ${agents.map(a=>`<tr><td><strong>${a.emoji} ${a.name}</strong></td><td>${a.role}</td><td><code>${a.schedule}</code></td><td><code>@Devin ${a.playbook}</code></td><td><code>${a.slack}</code></td></tr>`).join('')}
  </table>
  <div class="sop-h3">Triggering Agents from Jira</div>
  <table class="sop-table">
    <tr><th>Action in Jira</th><th>What happens</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Add label <code>devin</code> to any ticket</td><td>Hermes picks it up and implements it (runs the !implement playbook)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Add label <code>!write-tests</code></td><td>Argus generates tests from the acceptance criteria</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Add label <code>!design-review</code></td><td>Devin reviews the design against the codebase</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Assign ticket to Devin service account</td><td>Hermes picks it up with the default playbook</td></tr>
    <tr><td>@mention Devin in a comment</td><td>Devin starts a session using your comment as the prompt</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="sop-h3">Triggering Agents from Teams</div>
  <table class="sop-table">
    <tr><th>Teams message</th><th>What happens</th></tr>
    <tr><td><code>@Devin !review</code></td><td>Zeus reviews all open PRs immediately and posts findings</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>@Devin !implement PROJ-123</code></td><td>Hermes picks up that specific ticket and starts implementing</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>@Devin !test</code></td><td>Argus runs the full regression suite now</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>@Devin !release</code></td><td>Atlas runs the full release process now</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>@Devin !maintenance</code></td><td>Hephaestus runs a dependency and dead-code scan now</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>@Devin !security-review</code></td><td>Themis runs a security sweep now</td></tr>
    <tr><td><code>@Devin !ask [question]</code></td><td>Quick codebase Q&amp;A without starting a full session</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="sop-callout tip"><div class="sop-callout-icon">✅</div><div><strong>Override any running agent:</strong> Tag <code>@Devin</code> in the Teams thread for any running session to give new instructions, pause the agent, or redirect it. Send <code>EXIT</code> to end a session. Send <code>sleep</code> to pause it and come back later.</div></div>
</div>`},
{id:'setup',num:'§4',name:'Setup Checklist',render:()=>{
  const groups=[
    {title:'Admin Setup (Engineering Lead — ~3.5 hours)',items:[
      {id:'s1',text:'Connect GitHub: Settings → Integrations → GitHub → Connect all repos'},
      {id:'s2',text:'Connect Jira: Settings → Integrations → Jira → Connect, create Devin service account in Jira'},
      {id:'s3',text:'Connect Teams: Settings → Integrations → Microsoft Teams → Connect, invite Devin to all team channels'},
      {id:'s4',text:'Enable Devin Review: Settings → Review → Add all repos → toggle auto-review ON'},
      {id:'s5',text:'Index repos: Settings → Repositories → Index all repos (enables Ask Devin and DeepWiki)'},
      {id:'s6',text:'Create 6 Playbooks: !review, !implement, !test, !release, !maintenance, !security-review (see Agent Roster tab for prompts)'},
      {id:'s7',text:'Create 6 Scheduled Sessions with the cron schedules listed in the Agent Reference'},
      {id:'s8',text:'Create Automations: CI failure fixer, #incidents auto-triage, Themis security PR trigger'},
      {id:'s9',text:'Add Webhook Automation for CI/CD → Devin (post-deploy runbook updates)'},
      {id:'s10',text:'Set ACU limits per automation session to cap cost (recommended: 20 ACU per CI fix session)'},
      {id:'s11',text:'Configure each repo&#39;s <code>environment</code> (Blueprints) so sessions boot with deps installed and tests runnable'},
      {id:'s12',text:'Add <code>Secrets</code> agents need (test DB, API keys) — never in AGENTS.md or playbooks'},
      {id:'s13',text:'Turn on <code>Session Insights</code> and bookmark <code>Settings → Usage</code>; set ACU limits'},
      {id:'s14',text:'Lock down access: service-account least privilege, SSO, IP allowlist, audit-log review'}
    ]},
    {title:'Per-Repo Setup (Each Team Lead — ~30 min per repo)',items:[
      {id:'r1',text:'Add <code>AGENTS.md</code> to repo root: architecture conventions, module boundaries, naming patterns'},
      {id:'r2',text:'Add <code>REVIEW.md</code> to repo root: critical paths, security rules, anti-patterns, what to ignore'},
      {id:'r3',text:'Add <code>.agents/skills/implement/SKILL.md</code>: test commands, lint, branch naming, PR conventions'},
      {id:'r4',text:'Add <code>.agents/skills/test-before-pr/SKILL.md</code>: install, lint, test, build commands'},
      {id:'r5',text:'Create Jira labels: <code>devin</code> (implement), <code>!write-tests</code>, <code>!design-review</code>, <code>!security-review</code>'},
      {id:'r6',text:'Add Architecture Knowledge: Settings → Knowledge → Add (trigger: "architecture" or "API design")'}
    ]},
    {title:'Per-Engineer Setup (~5 min)',items:[
      {id:'e1',text:'Connect personal Teams account: Devin Settings → Integrations → Microsoft Teams → link your account'},
      {id:'e2',text:'Connect GitHub account: Devin Settings → Integrations → GitHub'},
      {id:'e3',text:'Self-enroll for auto-review: Settings → Review → "Add myself (@username)"'},
      {id:'e4',text:'Bookmark: app.devin.ai for session management, devinreview.com for fast PR review'}
    ]}
  ];
  return `<div class="sop-doc">
    <div class="sop-section-header">
      <div class="sop-section-num">Section 4</div>
      <div class="sop-section-name">Setup Checklist</div>
      <div class="sop-section-desc">One-time setup to activate all agents and integrations. Estimated total: ~3.5 hrs admin setup + 30 min per repo + 5 min per engineer.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="sop-callout tip"><div class="sop-callout-icon">✅</div><div>Check items off as you complete them — progress is saved in your browser. Print or screenshot this section to track setup progress with your team.</div></div>
    ${groups.map(g=>`
      <div class="sop-checklist-group">
        <div class="checklist-group-title">${g.title}</div>
        ${g.items.map(item=>`
          <div class="checklist-item" id="ci-${item.id}" onclick="toggleCheck('${item.id}')">
            <input type="checkbox" id="cb-${item.id}" onclick="event.stopPropagation()">
            <label for="cb-${item.id}">${item.text}</label>
          </div>`).join('')}
      </div>`).join('')}
  </div>`;
}},
{id:'rules',num:'§5',name:'Rules of Engagement',render:()=>`
<div class="sop-doc">
  <div class="sop-section-header">
    <div class="sop-section-num">Section 5</div>
    <div class="sop-section-name">Rules of Engagement</div>
    <div class="sop-section-desc">What you must do for agents to work well — and what breaks them.</div>
  </div>
  ${[
    {agent:'🪽 Hermes — Development',do:['Write acceptance criteria with explicit Definition of Done','Include technical context: relevant files, patterns to follow, constraints','Add <code>devin</code> label only when a ticket is truly ready — no open questions','Check <code>#dev-runs</code> each morning to see what Hermes built overnight','If Hermes asks a question in Teams, answer promptly — it is paused waiting'],dont:['Assign vague tickets ("improve performance", "fix the login bug")','Expect Hermes to infer product requirements not written in the ticket','Merge a Hermes PR without reading it — you are accountable for what ships','Label a blocked or ambiguous ticket as ready — Hermes will produce incorrect output']},
    {agent:'⚡ Zeus — Code Review',do:['Wait for Zeus\'s review comment before starting your human review','Act on Severe bug findings immediately — they are high-confidence real issues','Maintain <code>REVIEW.md</code> — this is Zeus\'s rulebook, not optional','Use Zeus\'s codebase-aware chat to ask questions about the diff before reviewing'],dont:['Dismiss Zeus\'s comments without reading them','Bypass branch protections to merge without review','Expect Zeus to know unwritten team conventions — write them in <code>REVIEW.md</code>','Ignore Zeus findings and leave them unresolved — resolve or dismiss with a reason']},
    {agent:'👁 Argus — QA',do:['Check <code>#qa-alerts</code> every morning — treat it like your daily standup update','Triage any new Jira tickets Argus files — they represent real regressions','Write acceptance criteria in testable form (Given/When/Then)','Keep test infrastructure healthy — Argus depends on a working test runner'],dont:['Ignore nightly failures — they compound into a backlog quickly','Delete tests to make coverage numbers look good','Disable failing tests without filing a Jira ticket explaining why','Let Argus file dozens of tickets without triaging — they become noise']},
    {agent:'🌍 Atlas — Release',do:['Close or defer all P1/P2 blockers before Friday — Atlas checks for them','Review and approve release notes before Atlas publishes externally','Keep Jira release versions up to date throughout the sprint','Monitor <code>#releases</code> and <code>#incidents</code> after each deploy'],dont:['Manually tag releases in GitHub — Atlas owns this, conflicts will occur','Edit Confluence release pages manually — Atlas will overwrite them on the next run','Trigger a manual <code>!release</code> mid-week without notifying the team','Skip the release approval step — Atlas will post a draft and wait for a human thumbs-up']}
  ].map(r=>`
    <div class="sop-h3">${r.agent}</div>
    <div class="sop-rules-grid">
      <div class="sop-rules-col">
        <div class="rules-col-head rules-head-do">✅ Do</div>
        ${r.do.map(d=>`<div class="rules-item"><div class="rules-pip-do"></div><span>${d}</span></div>`).join('')}
      </div>
      <div class="sop-rules-col">
        <div class="rules-col-head rules-head-dont">❌ Don't</div>
        ${r.dont.map(d=>`<div class="rules-item"><div class="rules-pip-dont"></div><span>${d}</span></div>`).join('')}
      </div>
    </div>`).join('')}
  <div class="sop-h3">Writing tickets agents can execute</div>
  <div class="sop-prose"><p>The acceptance criteria <em>is</em> the spec. A clear, verifiable ticket is the single biggest driver of agent success.</p></div>
  <div class="sop-rules-grid">
    <div class="sop-rules-col">
      <div class="rules-col-head rules-head-do">✅ Good ticket</div>
      <div class="rules-item"><div class="rules-pip-do"></div><span>Explicit Definition of Done + acceptance criteria, ideally Given / When / Then</span></div>
      <div class="rules-item"><div class="rules-pip-do"></div><span>Names the files / areas to touch and the patterns to follow</span></div>
      <div class="rules-item"><div class="rules-pip-do"></div><span>Verifiable: "CI passes", "endpoint returns X", a failing test to make green</span></div>
      <div class="rules-item"><div class="rules-pip-do"></div><span>Scoped to roughly a 3-hour task; larger work split into linked tickets</span></div>
    </div>
    <div class="sop-rules-col">
      <div class="rules-col-head rules-head-dont">❌ Bad ticket</div>
      <div class="rules-item"><div class="rules-pip-dont"></div><span>"Improve performance" / "fix the login bug" — no target, no repro</span></div>
      <div class="rules-item"><div class="rules-pip-dont"></div><span>Assumes product context that lives only in someone's head</span></div>
      <div class="rules-item"><div class="rules-pip-dont"></div><span>No way to tell whether it is done</span></div>
      <div class="rules-item"><div class="rules-pip-dont"></div><span>Huge, open-ended, or carrying unresolved open questions</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="sop-callout tip"><div class="sop-callout-icon">📎</div><div><strong>Templates &amp; examples:</strong> <a href="https://docs.devin.ai/essential-guidelines/good-vs-bad-instructions" target="_blank">Good vs. Bad Instructions</a> · <a href="https://docs.devin.ai/essential-guidelines/prompt-templates-cheat-sheet" target="_blank">Prompt Templates Cheat Sheet</a> · <a href="https://docs.devin.ai/essential-guidelines/when-to-use-devin" target="_blank">When to Use Devin</a></div></div>
  <div class="sop-h3">General Rules — All Agents</div>
  <div class="sop-callout warning"><div class="sop-callout-icon">⚠️</div><div><strong>Agents make mistakes.</strong> Always read PRs and review agent findings before merging. You remain accountable for everything that ships to production. An agent producing a bad PR is a signal to improve the playbook or acceptance criteria — not a reason to stop using agents.</div></div>
  <div class="sop-callout tip"><div class="sop-callout-icon">✅</div><div><strong>Improving agents over time:</strong> When an agent does something wrong, update its Playbook or add a Knowledge item. When it does something right that surprised you, add it to the Playbook too. The agents improve as the team invests in their prompts and context.</div></div>
  <div class="sop-callout info"><div class="sop-callout-icon">💡</div><div><strong>ACU budgets:</strong> Each agent session has a compute budget. If an agent stops mid-task, it may have hit the limit. Check Settings → Usage. Increase the ACU limit for complex tasks, or break the task into smaller Jira tickets.</div></div>
</div>`},
{id:'commands',num:'§6',name:'Quick Commands',render:()=>`
<div class="sop-doc">
  <div class="sop-section-header">
    <div class="sop-section-num">Section 6</div>
    <div class="sop-section-name">Quick Commands & Reference</div>
    <div class="sop-section-desc">Everything you need to interact with agents day-to-day. Bookmark this section.</div>
  </div>
  <div class="sop-h3">Teams Commands</div>
  <div class="cmd-group">
    <div class="cmd-table">
      <div class="cmd-row-key">@Devin !review</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Zeus: review all open PRs now, post summary to #code-review</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">@Devin !implement PROJ-123</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Hermes: pick up that specific Jira ticket and implement it</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">@Devin !test</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Argus: run full regression suite now, post results to #qa-alerts</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">@Devin !release</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Atlas: run the full release process now</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">@Devin !maintenance</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Hephaestus: run dependency scan and dead code removal now</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">@Devin !security-review</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Themis: run security sweep now, post to #security</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">@Devin !ask [question]</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Quick codebase Q&amp;A without starting a full agent session</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">@Devin !write-tests PROJ-456</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Generate tests from the acceptance criteria of that ticket</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">sleep</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Pause the agent in the current thread (send any message to wake)</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">EXIT</div><div class="cmd-row-val">End the current agent session entirely</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="sop-h3">Jira Labels</div>
  <div class="cmd-group">
    <div class="cmd-table">
      <div class="cmd-row-key">devin</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Hermes picks up and implements this ticket (runs the !implement playbook)</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">!write-tests</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Argus generates tests from acceptance criteria</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">!design-review</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Devin reviews the design against the codebase</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">!security-review</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Themis runs a security review on this ticket's scope</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="sop-h3">Agent Schedules (cron)</div>
  <div class="cmd-group">
    <div class="cmd-table">
      <div class="cmd-row-key">0 7 * * 1</div><div class="cmd-row-val">🔧 Hephaestus — Monday 7am: dependency scan, dead code, security audit</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">0 8 * * 1-5</div><div class="cmd-row-val">⚡ Zeus — Weekdays 8am: morning PR review digest to #code-review</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">0 9 * * 1-5</div><div class="cmd-row-val">🪽 Hermes — Weekdays 9am: picks up top 3 "Ready for Dev" tickets</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">0 10 * * 3</div><div class="cmd-row-val">⚖️ Themis — Wednesday 10am: weekly security &amp; compliance sweep</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">0 2 * * *</div><div class="cmd-row-val">👁 Argus — Every night 2am: full regression suite, files Jira bugs</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">0 9 * * 5</div><div class="cmd-row-val">🌍 Atlas — Friday 9am: changelog, GitHub release tag, Confluence update</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="sop-h3">Key Files in Every Repo</div>
  <div class="cmd-group">
    <div class="cmd-table">
      <div class="cmd-row-key">AGENTS.md</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Architecture conventions, module boundaries, naming rules. Devin reads this at the start of every session.</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">REVIEW.md</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Review guidelines: critical paths, security rules, anti-patterns, what to ignore. Zeus reads this on every PR review.</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">.agents/skills/implement/SKILL.md</div><div class="cmd-row-val">How to implement a feature: branch naming, test commands, PR conventions. Hermes follows this automatically.</div>
      <div class="cmd-row-key">.agents/skills/test-before-pr/SKILL.md</div><div class="cmd-row-val">Pre-PR checklist: install, lint, test, build. All agents invoke this before opening any PR.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="sop-callout tip"><div class="sop-callout-icon">📎</div><div><strong>Devin docs:</strong> <a href="https://docs.devin.ai" target="_blank" style="color:var(--teal)">docs.devin.ai</a> &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong>Devin app:</strong> <a href="https://app.devin.ai" target="_blank" style="color:var(--teal)">app.devin.ai</a> &nbsp;·&nbsp; <strong>Fast PR review:</strong> replace <code>github.com</code> with <code>devinreview.com</code> in any PR URL</div></div>
</div>`}
,
{id:'platform',num:'§7',name:'Platform & Governance',render:()=>`
<div class="sop-doc">
  <div class="sop-section-header">
    <div class="sop-section-num">Section 7</div>
    <div class="sop-section-name">Platform, Cost &amp; Governance</div>
    <div class="sop-section-desc">The operational layer under the agents — what a session is, what it costs, how to keep it secure, and the extra capabilities worth knowing.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="sop-h3">Cost &amp; usage</div>
  <table class="sop-table">
    <tr><th>Lever</th><th>What to know</th></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>ACU</strong></td><td>Agent Compute Units meter every session. Watch them in <code>Settings → Usage</code>.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>ACU limits</strong></td><td>Cap per-session spend on automations / schedules (e.g. 20 ACU per CI fix). A session that stops mid-task may have hit its cap.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Free credits</strong></td><td>Up to $50 in usage credits when you first connect GitHub.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Session Insights</strong></td><td>Per-session analysis + feedback — your loop for improving prompts and playbooks.</td></tr>
  </table>

  <div class="sop-h3">Access &amp; security</div>
  <table class="sop-table">
    <tr><th>Control</th><th>Use it to</th></tr>
    <tr><td>RBAC / custom roles</td><td>Limit who can change playbooks, schedules, org settings; scope the service account to least privilege.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>SSO (SAML / OIDC / Okta / Azure)</td><td>Enforce company identity for all Devin access.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>IP access lists</td><td>Restrict web + API access to office / VPN ranges.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Audit logs</td><td>Review every agent and admin action.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Secrets</td><td>Hold credentials agents need — never in <code>AGENTS.md</code> or playbooks.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Kill switch</td><td><code>EXIT</code> in Teams, or terminate a session in the web app / API.</td></tr>
  </table>
  <div class="sop-callout info"><div class="sop-callout-icon">🔧</div><div>Configure all of this in the Setup Guide — the <strong>Environment &amp; Secrets</strong> and <strong>Access &amp; Security</strong> sections.</div></div>

  <div class="sop-h3">Local development → cloud</div>
  <table class="sop-table">
    <tr><th>Path</th><th>How</th></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Devin Desktop</strong> (Cascade)</td><td>Plan in Cascade → <em>Send to Devin</em> in the Agent Command Center → cloud session continues while you keep coding.</td></tr>
    <tr><td><strong>Devin CLI</strong></td><td><code>curl -fsSL https://cli.devin.ai/install.sh | bash</code>, then <code>/handoff</code> to push a longer task to cloud Devin.</td></tr>
  </table>

  <div class="sop-h3">More features worth knowing</div>
  <table class="sop-table">
    <tr><th>Feature</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Slash commands</td><td>Insert predefined prompt templates inside a session.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>PR templates</td><td>Hermes fills out your repo's GitHub PR template automatically.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Autofix / bot settings</td><td>Control which bots Devin responds to on PRs.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Testing &amp; video recordings</td><td>Devin records video proof of the end-to-end tests it ran.</td></tr>
    <tr><td>MCP / Devin MCP</td><td>Give agents extra tools via MCP servers, or drive Devin from other MCP clients.</td></tr>
  </table>
</div>`}
];

